rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that links a dedicated work, the person who dedicates it, the person to whom it is dedicated, and the content of the dedication.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dedication

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates the dedication to the work that was dedicated
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Work Dedicated

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The dedicatee of the work. This will be one or more people, a group of people, or an organization of some kind.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dedicatee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The agent that dedicated the creative work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dedicator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The text of the dedication itself. Sometimes dedications include more than just a name (e.g. \"to X, my friend and mentor\"), or the dedicatee might be called by something other than their given name (e.g. \"to my mother\"), or the dedication might not be to a specific entity (e.g. \"dedicated to you, the reader\").
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dedication Notes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The person who dedicated the creative work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dedicator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a person to a dedication written by that person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dedication

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity type representing the collecion of all design patterns. These are primarily used in architecture and computer science and are the well-known, formalized solutions to design problems in a particular field.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Design Pattern

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Devices by which people can consume content, e.g. listen to audio files, read ebooks, play videos, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Device

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all discussion threads. Discussions threads are a feature of many email clients, online newsgroups and forums that aid users by grouping messages by topic and replies to messages.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discussion Thread

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:media_common.discussion_thread to the internet.internet_forum in which the thread is a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Forum

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:media_common.discussion_thread to the mso:common.text entity that is one of the posts in this thread.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Post

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:media_common.discussion_thread to its type, like 'talk'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Thread Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:media_common.discussion_thread to the last date is was updated, including new messages and posts or edits to pre-existing messages or posts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Updated

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A creative work that is complete and was finished either by the original author or artist or by someone else after the original author or artist died.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Finished work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a finished work to the original unfinished work that it is based on.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Completion of Work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Creative works that are no longer availabe for some reason, e.g. because of fire, theft, destruction by owner, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lost work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The reason that the given creative work was lost. More specific information can be entered in the description property for the object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reason for Loss

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date that the work was lost.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Lost

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all media episodes. Episodes are those pieces of media content that are part of a serial and have a cohesive storyline.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Episode

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A general category describing the form, style or subject matter of a creative work, e.g. science fiction, romance, thriller, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Media Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a media genre to a broadcaster whose content can be (partially) described with the genre.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Broadcaster

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a genre to one of its subgenres.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Child Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a genre to a creative work that exemplifies the genre. Note that this property should eventually be defined as a virtual property, which is the inverse of mso:media_common.creative_work.genre.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Creative Work

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a genre to another genre that subsumes it, i.e. is broader in meaning that the given genre.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity type representing the collection of all news reports. News reports are the short accounts of news happenings reported. This primary entity includes written and oral reports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: News Report

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:media_common.news_report to the date the new report was either published or aired.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reporting Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:media_common.news_report to the mso:organization.organization that is the organization responsible for its content.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reporting Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing fictional identities of real people that are assumed for the purpose of authoring creative works, e.g. novels.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pseudonym

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a fictional identity of a person to the real person having this identity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Person

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A pithy sentence that was uttered or written by an historical figure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quotation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The person, character, or group that the quotation was addressed to. Many quotations do not have an explicit addressee, and this property should be left empty in those cases. Implicit addressees, such as "the audience" or "the reader" should not be entered as values.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Addressee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a quotation to the person who said or wrote the quotation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Author

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: If the given quotation is from a work of fiction, the character who uttered the quotation can be entered here.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spoken by Character

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date that the given quotation was written or uttered.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quotation Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: People to whom this quote is commonly and wrongly ascribed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Incorrect Attribution

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a quotation to the creative work (book, film, essay, etc.) in which the quotation appears.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quotation Source

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a quotation to the subject of the quotation, e.g. John Kennedy, World War II, Seattle, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The person, character, or group that a quotation was addressed to. Many quotations do not have an explicit addressee, and implicit addressees, such as \"the audience\" or \"the reader\" do not count as instances of this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quotation Addressee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quotation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Creative works from which quotations are taken.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A thing, person, event or other entity that is the topic of a creative work, e.g. John Kennedy, World War II, Seattle, etc. This is a very broad type and should probably be deprecated at some point in favor of mso:type.object.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a subject to a quotation that exemplifies the subject.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quotation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:media_common.subject to known researchers of the subject. A researcher can be a person or organization, and the agent is known for doing systematic investigations into the subject or a search for knowledge about the subject.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Researcher

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:media_common.subject to its sub-topics. Examples of this property include like women's health is a sub-topic of health, and retirement planninng is a sub-topic of personal finance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sub-topic

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:media_common.subject to a website that contains relevant content for the subject.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Webpage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An outline or summary of a larger creative work.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Synopsis

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Completions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all urban legends. These are the stories of modern folklore, those stories that spread spontaneously with slight variations in form and are usually false.
